Ethnic unrest erupted in the last years of the Soviet Union .
The Kremlin dispatched troops to check the violence generated by some of the USSR 's more than 100 ethnic groups .
The ethnic unrest proliferated after the Soviet Union 's demise .
Serious ethnic-driven fighting occurred in Armenia , Azerbaijan , Georgia , Khirghizia , Kazakhstan , Uzbekistan , Tajikistan and Moldavia , One hundred thousand were killed in Tajikistan .
In late 1992 Russia sent troops to the Caucasus and Tajikistan .
The international community feared the destabilization of the former Soviet Union .
In 1944 there was a call for a restored Soviet Union To deal with ethnicity .
